Bug.WithStack:
Description: Chinese characters can't be previewed in Eclipse version 3.1 with 
local data source.

Steps to reproduce:
1. Create a local data source in which there are chinese characters.
2. Preview.

Actual result: you will find "???" is displayed.
I write a test as the following:
public void test1() throws Exception{
	Class.forName("sun.jdbc.odbc.JdbcOdbcDriver");
	Connection connection = DriverManager.getConnection("jdbc:odbc:test");
	PreparedStatement pStatement = connection.prepareStatement("select * 
from Account");
	ResultSet rs =  pStatement.executeQuery();
	ResultSetMetaData rsdm =  rs.getMetaData();
	while ( rs.next( ) )
	{
		for ( int i = 1; i <= rsdm.getColumnCount( ); i++ )
		{
			System.out.print( rs.getString( i ) + "\t" );
		}
		System.out.print( "\n" );
	}
}
Run it in XP, locale US, language for non-Unicode programs English(US)
The result is:
/***********************************************************/
1	test	2001-10-10 00:00:00	10.0000	null	
2	dfadfa	2001-10-11 00:00:00	222222.0000	null	
3	ddd	2001-10-10 00:00:00	222121.0000	null	
4	dddd	2001-10-10 00:00:00	70.0000	null	
5	????	2001-11-20 00:00:00	1213132.0000	null	
6	a	2001-11-21 00:00:00	1000000.0000	null	
7	v	2001-11-23 00:00:00	200.0000	null	
8	adaf	2001-12-01 00:00:00	121.0000	null	
9	ssss	2001-12-12 00:00:00	200.0000	null	
10	tests	2001-10-31 00:00:00	20.2100	null	
11	sql	null	.0000	null	
/***********************************************************/

In the fifth line, what we expect are four chinese characters.
In the case you described, data engine of Birt depends on the data from jdbc, 
so we have nothing to do about it.
I believe it is not a bug of BIRT.
Verified in build 20050720.

